# Tools Watchlist — Agent Rules

When Jon pastes a **GitHub/repo URL**, says **review tool**, **evaluate tool**, **add to watchlist**, **review batch**, **review design**, or **review session done**:

## Fleet scope (mandatory)

- **JonBeatz is the review desk, not the knowledge base.** Grades, setup status, and accepted tools belong to the **entire Hermes fleet**.
- **Write canonical first:** `D:\Hermes\projects\_core-scripts\shared-profile-content\` (docs, skills, scripts, rules, prompts).
- **Then mirror:** `npm run sync:docs -- -Write` → profile `.cursor/docs/`.
- **Then propagate:** `npm run fleet:sync` from hub when skills/scripts/rules/prompts changed.
- **Never** persist tool grades only under JonBeatz without updating shared `TOOLS-*.md`.
- Policy doc: [FLEET-TOOLS-KNOWLEDGE.md](../docs/FLEET-TOOLS-KNOWLEDGE.md)

## Canonical docs (Hermes-wide)

| Doc | Path |
|-----|------|
| Watchlist + grades | `D:\Hermes\projects\_core-scripts\shared-profile-content\docs\TOOLS-WATCHLIST.md` |
| Setup status (READY vs keys) | `...\docs\TOOLS-SETUP-STATUS.md` |
| Full research | `...\docs\TOOLS-REFERENCE.md` |
| Verify commands | `...\docs\TOOLS-SETUP-STATUS.md` → Post-install verify registry |

| Prompt | When |
|--------|------|
| [Review-Tool.md](../prompts/Review-Tool.md) | Single, batch, design grade, re-review |
| [Review-Session-Done.md](../prompts/Review-Session-Done.md) | **review session done** |

## Policy (Jon 2026-07-04, v2 2026-07-13)

1. **Additive only** — never disable or replace working stack (Mem0, DeepSeek, ComfyUI, MCPs).
2. **Overlap OK** — strong alternatives on deck still earn ADOPT / IN USE.
3. **OSS/free first** — minimal paid OK when ROI is high.
4. **Install gate** — IN USE only after Jon approves (or says "run install now").
5. **Doc threshold** — only **B- (80+) and above** persist to watchlist / setup-status / reference. C+ and below: grade in chat only unless Jon asks.
6. **Grades first** — full review block in chat **before** any `AskQuestion` install prompt.
7. **Duplicate pre-check** — run `npm run tools:review-precheck` or grep TOOLS-* / DESIGN-REFERENCES before research; skip unless **re-review**.
8. **Batch mode** — multiple URLs → all grade blocks first → one scoreboard → **one** install AskQuestion.
9. **Security gate** — mandatory `security-review` subagent for auth/deploy/agent-config-writing tools.
10. **Risks required** — every review includes Windows/ports/VRAM/license/auto-install gotchas.

## Required outputs per review

1. Letter grade (A+→F) + score /100 + one-line summary (use fixed template in Review-Tool.md)
2. Verdict: IN USE | ADOPT | WATCH | SKIP
3. Setup status: READY | PARTIAL | NEEDS_KEY | NEEDS_LOGIN | NOT_INSTALLED
4. Gap, Overlap, **Risks**, Verify, Recommendation
5. Update **shared canonical** docs in `_core-scripts/shared-profile-content/docs/` → `npm run sync:docs -- -Write`
6. If install added skills/scripts/rules → shared skeleton + `npm run fleet:sync` (hub)
7. **Only then** — install AskQuestion (single or batch)
8. Post-install: verify registry command → flip Setup READY/PARTIAL in **shared** TOOLS-SETUP-STATUS
9. Optional: `draven:add` + vault on ADOPT→IN USE (link canonical row, do not duplicate full grade table)

## Re-grade policy

- **WATCH:** 6 months or major version
- **IN USE:** breakage/upgrade or Jon **re-review**
- **ADOPT:** before install if row >3 months old

## Quick status

```powershell
npm run tools:review-precheck -- "name-or-url"
npm run tools:status
```
